cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D semantic segmentation benchmarks and 3D-video perception. It could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as robotics and VR/AR applications are mentioned in the abstract. The paper proposes a new method for spatio-temporal perception using convolutional neural networks, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of sparse tensors, which could be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
